Chile Stocks: Embotelladora Andina, Empresas La Polar and Sonda

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-07-07T21:19:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-07/chilean-stocks-aes-gener-embotelladora-andina-la-polar-sonda.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:12 p.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index closed little changed at 4,776.59.  Embotelladora Andina SA (AKO/A)   gained 1.6 percent to
2,265 pesos, the biggest gain in two weeks. Chile’s largest
Coca-Cola bottler was rated “overweight” at the brokerage unit
of Banco de Credito e Inversiones.  Empresas La Polar SA (LAPOLAR)   increased 3.4 percent to
634.38 pesos. The department-store operator under investigation
for consumer loan irregularities rose for a third day as
shareholders prepare to vote tomorrow for a new board of
directors.  Sonda SA (SONDA)   advanced 0.1 percent to 1,297.6 pesos.
Chile’s largest information technology company had its 12-month
price target increased to 1,533 pesos from 927 pesos at
Santiago-based brokerage Celfin Capital SA, which also
reiterated a “buy” rating.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
 ethomson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  